title: Matt Kenseth wins NASCAR pole
text:
Matt Kenseth wins NASCAR pole Oct. 8, 2015 9:08 p.m. (0) Comments 
Matt Kenseth claimed the pole Thursday night for the NASCAR Sprint Cup Series race Saturday at Charlotte Motor Speedway in Concord, N.C. 
The 2013 champion from Cambridge turned a lap at 194.532 mph to edge fellow Chase for the Sprint Cup contender and Joe Gibbs Racing teammate Kyle Busch and sweep the poles at Charlotte this season. 
It is Kenseth's fourth pole of 2015 and 17th overall. 
Joey Logano qualified third for Saturday night's Bank of America 500, and non-Chase driver Greg Biffle was fourth. 
Among the other contenders who'll start in the top 10 are Kurt Busch in sixth, Carl Edwards in eighth and Ryan Newman in 10th. Kevin Harvick , who raced his way into Round 2 with a clutch win last week, will start 11th, and Dale Earnhardt Jr. begins 12th. 
Only three of the 12 drivers remaining in the Chase didn't make it to the final round of qualifying — Brad Keselowski (starts 13th), Martin Truex (15th) and Jeff Gordon (22nd). 
Eau Claire's Paul Menard , who was eliminated from the Chase, will start 26th. © 2015 , Journal Sentinel Inc. All rights reserved.
